<h2> Definition </h2>

The <strong>@HI{{aida}}</strong> clause expresses the idea of "while" or "during".
<p></p>

<h2> Examples </h2>

<h2> Notes </h2>

The subjects in the <strong>@HI{{aida}}</strong> clause and the main clause can be the same or different.
If they are different, the subject in the <strong>@HI{{aida}}</strong> clause is marked by @HI{{ga}} and not by @HI{{ha}}.
<p></p>

The verb before <strong>@HI{{aida}}</strong> is either @Vte{{}}@HI{{iru}} or @HI{{iru}}.
<p></p>

If the <strong>@HI{{aida}}</strong> clause is followed by @HI{{ni}} then the time span of the main clause
falls within that of the <strong>@HI{{aida}}</strong> clause. Otherwise the two clauses are expected
to cover the same span of time.
<p></p>

